\section*{Inverse Matrix of the Response Matrix}

We denote the response matrix defined by equations (\ref{eq. res_mtrx}), (\ref{eq. diag}), and (\ref{eq. off-diag}) as $\mathbf{R}$.
$\mathbf{R}$ is a triangular matrix.
Figure \ref{fig. nonzero} displays the nonzero elements of $\mathbf{R}$.
The columns with nonzero off-diagonal elements shift rightward every two rows because the magnitude relation (\ref{eq. increments}) holds.
